<u>Littleton Tragedy</u>

April 20, 1999

Eric Harris (18 y.o.) and Dylan Klebold (17 y.o.) walked into Columbine High School
in Littleton, CO, armed with shotguns, TEC 9 semiautomatic, pipe bombs and a 9mm
semiautomatic rifle. Around 11am, the two boys opened fire on teachers and students
killing 13 innocents. The massacre was over around 4pm, when police found the two
boys in the school library, dead from their own hands.

During this massacre, Cassie Bernall (17), Steven Curnow (14), Corey DePooeter (17),
Kelly Fleming (16), Matthew Kechter (16), Daniel Mauser (15), Danny Rohrbough (15),
Dave Sanders (47), Rachel Scott (17), Isaiah Shoels (18), John Tomlin (16), Lauren
Townsend (18), and Kyle Velasquez were lost.

In the days after, several hackers have changed web pages to make statements about
the events on April 20. They can be seen here.

